node.accessibility_caption: Photo by GAMINGbible on August 23, 2021. May be an image of dog, outdoors and text that says 'G E U/LIEW78 'THE WITCHER 3' FAN BUILDS PLACE OF POWER AS A MEMORIAL TO THEIR DOG'.

node.text:
"I made a place of power as a memorial for my dog who passed away. He always kept me company while playing TW3" 💜

Reddit user Lieuw78 played 'The Witcher 3: Wild Hunt' with their dog Indi by their side.

Sadly, Indi passed away recently, and to help process the loss, Lieuw78 had an idea. They took one of the boulders found on a river trail that the two of them used to walk together. A drill was used to create lots of holes in the stone which then became one large smooth hole with the use of a grinder. Then, they wrote their dog's name in Elvish on the stone and placed it in their garden. The result is a personalised replica of a Place of Power from The Witcher 3, honouring Indi's character and companionship throughout their life
